    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "good_prompt",
      "prompt": "You are an empathetic HR Manager at a tech startup. Write a rejection email to a candidate who reached the final interview stage but was not selected. Maintain a professional yet warm tone, provide constructive feedback on their coding test, and encourage them to apply for future roles.",
      "response": "Subject: Update on Your Application\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview with our team. We appreciate the effort you put into preparing for our conversations and submitting your coding test. \n\nWe were impressed by your background and experience, but after careful consideration, we have decided not to move forward with your application at this time. \n\nWe received a strong signal in your test that you have solid foundation in programming concepts, but there were some areas where we felt you could further improve, particularly in problem-solving strategies. \n\nWe encourage you to continue honing your skills and staying up-to-date with industry developments. We wish you the best in your job search and welcome you to apply for future openings that may be a better fit.",
